  <h1>Thermodynamics</h1>
  <p>Concepts that power the universe!</p>

  <h2>What is Thermodynamics?</h2>
  <p>Thermodynamics is the branch of physics that deals with heat and temperature, and their relation to energy and work.</p>

  <h2>Important Laws:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Zeroth Law:</strong> If A = B and B = C, then A = C.</li>
    <li><strong>First Law:</strong> Energy can neither be created nor destroyed.</li>
    <li><strong>Second Law:</strong> Heat cannot spontaneously flow from cold to hot body.</li>
    <li><strong>Third Law:</strong> Entropy approaches a constant value as temperature approaches absolute zero.</li>
  </ul>

